The paper discusses the development of a Multi User Adaptive Test System (MUATS) using fuzzy logic. This involves the use of psychometric models and item selection strategies applicable to adaptive testing processes. The paper also mentions the integration of the system with a GSM network and the use of Short Messaging Service (SMS). Based on these aspects, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.LG (machine learning), as they deal with the development of intelligent systems and models. The use of fuzzy logic also suggests the possibility of cs.CE (computational engineering) and cs.IT (information theory) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of the system being user-friendly and platform-independent suggests the possibility of cs.HC (human-computer interaction) sub-category.
